<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 2:27PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A cluster of strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
southern Scotland into southeastern Moore, southeastern Richmond and
Hoke Counties through 315 PM EDT...
At 226 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms near Aberdeen, or 9 miles south of Southern Pines,
moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Southern Pines, Raeford, Pinehurst, Hamlet, Aberdeen,
Hoffman, Whispering Pines, Pinebluff and Dobbins Heights.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
